      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 175°C fan. Butter and line the loaf tin. In a large bowl, mash the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "overripe",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9yesyw00009kv4war1yd79"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " {{banana}}s thoroughly with a fork until no large lumps remain. Beat in the {{light-brown-sugar}}, {{eggs}}, melted {{unsalted-butter}}, and {{vanilla-extract}}. Add the {{plain-flour}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}} and fold until just combined. Fold in the {{walnuts}} if using.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 55 to 58 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the batter into the tin. Bake for 55 to 58 minutes until the top is deeply coloured and cracked, and a skewer inserted into the centre comes out clean. If the top is browning before the centre is set, lay a piece of foil loosely over the tin. Cool in the tin for 15 minutes, then turn out onto a rack. Wait until completely cold before slicing, the crumb sets as it cools.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
